  "local_port": 60594,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "My viber on PC doesnt connect to internet. whats the problem? It shows me the messages that other send me but I cant reply through my pc.",
  "response": "If your Viber on PC is not connecting to the internet properly and you can view messages but can't reply, there could be several reasons for this issue. Here are some troubleshooting steps you can follow to resolve the problem:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Check Your Internet Connection**\n   - Ensure your PC is connected to the internet.\n   - Open a browser and check if other websites or services are working.\n   - If the internet is slow or unstable, try restarting your router or switching to a different network (e.g., mobile hotspot).\n\n---\n\n### **2. Update Viber**\n   - Make sure you\u2019re using the latest version of Viber for PC.\n   - Go to [Viber\u2019s official website](https://www.viber.com) and download the latest version if needed.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Restart Viber**\n   - Close Viber completely and reopen it.\n   - If it\u2019s running in the background, use Task Manager (Ctrl + Shift + Esc) to end the process and relaunch the app.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Log Out and Log Back In**\n   - Go to **Settings** in Viber and log out of your account.\n   - Log back in using the same phone number and verify your account with the code sent to your mobile device.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Check Firewall or Antivirus Settings**\n   - Your firewall or antivirus software might be blocking Viber\u2019s connection to the internet.\n   - Add Viber to the list of allowed applications in your firewall or antivirus settings.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Clear Viber Cache**\n   - Viber\u2019s cache might be corrupted, causing connection issues.\n   - Go to **Settings** \u2192 **Privacy** \u2192 **Clear Cache** and try again.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Reinstall Viber**\n   - Uninstall Viber from your PC.\n   - Restart your computer.\n   - Download and install the latest version from the official website.\n\n---\n\n### **8. Sync Your Device**\n   - Open the Viber app on your mobile device, go to **Settings** \u2192 **Viber on Desktop**, and ensure your PC is synced.\n\n---\n\n### **9. Check Viber\u2019s Server Status**\n   - Viber\u2019s servers might be down.\n   - Check Viber\u2019s official [Twitter account](https://twitter.com/viber) or [status page](https://status.viber.com) for any ongoing issues.\n\n---\n\n### **10. Contact Viber Support**\n   - If none of the above steps work, contact Viber\u2019s [Customer Support](https://support.viber.com/) for further assistance.\n\n---\n\nLet me know if you need help with any specific step!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
